sentences.en: A successful test case is one that detects an as - yet undiscovered error.
sentences.cn: 已找出新错误的测试样本才是成功的测试样本.

sentences.en: As tropical, as quaint, as any undiscovered island.
sentences.cn: 象任何热带的奇异的未被开发的岛屿一样.

sentences.en: Aspiring filmmakers, are you feeling overlooked , underappreciated, and undiscovered?
sentences.cn: 雄心勃勃的电影制片者, 你们是否觉得受人忽视 、 不被欣赏、遭到埋没?

sentences.en: Astronomers expect yet - undiscovered Kuiper Belt objects may rival even Pluto.
sentences.cn: 天文学家预计柯依伯带中可能会发现比冥王星大的天体.

sentences.en: At last the prospectors struck on an undiscovered gold mine.
sentences.cn: 勘探者们最终发现了一处别人未曾涉足过的金矿.

sentences.en: If something wrong is discovered, It'should be undiscovered immediately.
sentences.cn: 如果不好的东西被发现了, 就应该立即把它隐藏起来.

sentences.en: Inevitably , System Testing reveals errors which were undiscovered during Integration testing.
sentences.cn: 系统测试会发现集成测试中未发现的错误.

sentences.en: The name Vulcan was given to the undiscovered planet.
sentences.cn: 一颗不为人知的行星被命名为“祝融”。

sentences.en: The Problem on remaining crime undiscovered was a controversial issue.
sentences.cn: 余罪问题是个有争议的问题.

sentences.en: There seems to be still some elements undiscovered yet.
sentences.cn: 似乎仍然有一些元素没被发现.

sentences.en: This area is widely an undiscovered frontier.
sentences.cn: 这一领域是广泛的未被发现的前沿.

sentences.en: This site remained undiscovered, though long sought, until recent times.
sentences.cn: 虽经长期寻找，但该遗址直到最近才被发现。

sentences.en: Until 30 years ago, it had lain undiscovered , unmined and uninhabited.
sentences.cn: 直到30年前, 这块大陆还未被人发现、未被开采,也无人居住.

sentences.en: With earth - based telescopes many stars remain undiscovered.
sentences.cn: 即使使用地球上的高倍望远镜,许多星球仍然无法被发现.

trans.tran_en: Something that is undiscovered has not been discovered or noticed
